name: Ziplining and Ropes Course Adventure
description: Come visit High Trek Adventures for an unforgettable NorthWest experience.  Conveniently located just 25 minutes N of Seattle, you won't want to miss this high ropes course and ziplining activity.  You'll use the latest European technology and receive 20 minutes of ground school training before embarking on your self-led adventure.  The High Trek Challenge course includes 60+ obstacles and 3 zip lines and from any platform you can go three different directions so you get to choose your own adventure.  This is a great family activity for all ages.  Toddlers can move independently on the Cadet Course (but no ziplining for them).  Youth 7-10 can do everything so long as they are accompanied by an adult.  There is a nearby playground for toddlers and an 18 hole mini golf course.

review.name: Horrible horrible place
review.reviewBody:
Firstly we played golf….. don’t waste your money. All the turf was torn up and you cannot even play any good mini golf. 

This place lacked any safety. I sat up on top screaming for the guys to come help my son down. No one budged   They stood all together cokin ans jokin. I SCREAMED for 15 minutes trying to get attention of someone. Finally someone came to help and then we all get down. There was another child trying to get down from the rope course asking for help. The guy sat on his stool on his phone. I literally had to say hey man the kid needs help. Like do your job! 

Such a shame I spent over 100 dollars for such a bad wait not HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE!!!!!!!

review.name: Cass review
review.reviewBody: It was awesome! We got the adventure pass did the zip line, laser tag, ax throwing, and mini golf was there about 5 hours. Staff was great. Great place to social distance. Great place for birthdays.

review.name: Adventure course
review.reviewBody: It was a blast. We felt very safe and secure! My kids loved it! We needed to get out the house. This was great!

review.name: Too many people
review.reviewBody: There were a lot more people on the course than we were expecting, we almost left upon arrival. The employees did not seem to do anything to encourage social distancing between guests. The ropes course and ziplining itself was fine.

review.name: GREAT!
review.reviewBody: Love this place! An excellent selection of activities for the entire family. We’ve been many times and even had my daughters birthday party here a few years ago. This is exactly why we felt it safe for our first outing post social distancing. All the new protocol was great, but they didn’t do much to enforce other people from coming close to you (objectively out of their control) or ask us any screening questions. I just found that interesting as online it was very clear that everything would be followed to a T and be greatly enforced. All that being said, we will be back again and plan to reserve a time for axe throwing soon.

review.name: Love high ropes course
review.reviewBody: So glad they are open for 2020 season. We came here a couple times last summer. Always fun and never boring. The course is fun and such a reward to make it to the ziplines. Open air and wearing gloves - a great activity for crazy times.

review.name: Birthday fun
review.reviewBody: Super happy you guys were open, as it was my youngest daughters 11th birthday. We were suppose to be in Disneyland but it was canceled due to the virus so all we wanted was to make her day as special as we could. Your staff was amazing and great at keeping us safe. Yet helping us HAVE FUN. thanks again.

review.name: Good fun
review.reviewBody: Staff were professional, friendly, and helpful; check-in and introduction were easy and the course was fun and challenging!

review.name: 6 year old boys loved it.
review.reviewBody: I believe his name was Shannon. He was great with my boys. (6 yrs old). He made it fun and not intimidating for them learning the safety procedure, which was huge since they jumped right in rather than being hesitant to get started. Definitely will going back this summer.

review.name: Family bonding time at its best
review.reviewBody: We were all together as a family for the holidays so we wanted to make amazing memories.  This place delivers.  The athletic kids challenged themselves with harder courses.  The timid kids overcame fears and pushed themselves.  The 10 year old was tall enough to do the course himself.  I love that you are doubly safe with their safety system. In a 90 minute session, I was able to climb the course and ride the zip line down 3 times.

itemListElement.name: Day Hike with Views 20 Minutes from Seattle

name: Day Hike with Views 20 Minutes from Seattle
description:
Come hike through Squak Mountain State Park to get a stunning glimpse of Mt. Rainier! Rainier is Washington state's most iconic mountain and a must see on any trip to Seattle. Beside the view of the mountain we will enjoy the quiet wooded areas and several other viewpoints along the way. This hike will leave you feeling as if you are hours outside the city yet it is only 20 MINUTES FROM DOWNTOWN SEATTLE. 

The hike climbs moderately up to the viewpoints with some more inclined sections. The trail will take us through dense woodlands about 6 miles round trip (11 Kilometers). I will provide information about the area which was formally an RV camp ground recently turned into part of the state park. This trail is perfect for all levels, whether you are just getting into hiking or have been doing it for years. No matter what you are sure to enjoy this experience! The meeting location can be accessed by car or bus (554 Express). Transportation also available for a small fee.

itemListElement.name: Face-to-Face with the Glaciers of Rainier

name: Face-to-Face with the Glaciers of Rainier
description:
This hike avoids the crowds that throng the trails that start from Mt. Rainier's visitor centers. 

Instead, this little-known and hard-to-reach trail is in the Glacier View Wilderness of the Gifford Pinchot National Forest, immediately to the West of Mt. Rainier National Park. The lookout from this trail rivals any views of the mountain from within the park. You get up close and personal to Mt. Rainier and her south-facing glaciers in relative (and perhaps total) solitude.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Sightseeing City Tour With Lunch

name: Seattle Sightseeing City Tour With Lunch
description: Get a comprehensive tour of Seattle in a single day on this whirlwind excursion. This is a great option for those short on time or first-time visitors to the city. Learn about the history, art, culture, and architecture of the city through guided commentary. Stops include the Space Needle, Pike Place Market, and the Chihuly Museum, among others. All entrance fees are at your own expense.

name: 4-Hour Seattle City Tour
description: Seattle is famous for its bustling waterfront, numerous green spaces, and historic neighborhoods. Ideal for first-time visitors, this sightseeing tour provides an overview of top attractions such as Pioneer Square, the Space Needle, and Pike’s Place market. Sit back and relax while your guide provides historical and cultural background for each destination, and enjoy stops to walk and take photos.
